The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Medeira may replace 

De Ridder

A STAFF REPORTER

Calcutta: It seems that East Bengal will wait till their Super Cup match versus National League champions Mahindra United on May 27 to decide the fate of their Belgian coach Philippe de Ridder. According to a source, Salgaocar coach Savio Medeira is in contention for the post if the Belgian is shown the door. It is learnt that decision has been put off for the time being, keeping in view the clubs Super Cup tie. 

In a marathon two-hour meeting, the East Bengal officials discussed the budget for the season and the recruitment policy of the club on Tuesday. We are interested in keeping the squad intact, secretary Kalyan Majumdar told the reporters after the meeting. Secretary apart, the meeting was attended by president Pranab Dasgupta. 




